HEADWORD: Wonderwork
<hw>Won"der*work`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>wundorweorc</ets>.]</ety> <def>A wonderful work or act; a prodigy;
a miracle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such as in strange land⟦br⟧
He found in <qex>wonderworks</qex> of God and Nature's hand.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wonder-worker</ent>⟦br⟧
